    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Boston</placeName>. <date>July 13, 1854</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Respected friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I have received another<lb/> case of your books, and have
                expected<lb/> according to promise to hear from<lb/> you in reference to their
                disposal,<lb/> you will therefore please write<lb/> me by return of mail what
                you<lb/> want done with them, how many<lb/> you want me to send to
                Provid-<lb/>dence, and to what parties. I<lb/> have also in hands $10.00 from<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Kingsbury</persName> for his bible, and<lb/> $14.00 from <persName>Mr.
                    Bornstien</persName> for a<lb/> bible (8.00) and 2 years subscription<lb/>
                (6.00) to the “Occident.” You will also please<lb/> credit me with $1.62 for
                freight<lb/> for the cases. Hoping to hear from<lb/> you by return of mail.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">I remain respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Your <sic>freind</sic></p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">Henry S. Spier</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S. If you wish I will send you what<lb/> money I have on hand by express.</p>
        </body>
